The United States Government has been actively responding to the Kaseya ransomware incident since Friday. The FBI and CISA have been collaborating with Kaseya to assist impacted victims and conduct outreach. President Biden has directed the government to fully investigate the incident. The cybersecurity professionals from the FBI, CISA, and intelligence community have been working tirelessly to respond to the incident. Anyone who believes their systems have been compromised is urged to report to the Internet Crime Complaint Center. The FBI and CISA will provide assistance to identified victims based on the assessment of national risk. It is also recommended to follow Kaseya's guidance and implement mitigation techniques from CISA and FBI.